President Donald J. Trump has declared a major disaster in the State of Connecticut, ordering Federal assistance to supplement state, tribal, and local recovery efforts following severe storms, tornadoes, and straight-line winds on May 15, 2018. Federal funding will be available for emergency work, facility repairs, and hazard mitigation measures. James N. Russo has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for Federal recovery operations in the affected areas. Additional designations may be made in the future based on further damage assessments. For more information, contact the FEMA News Desk.